@Database

@node MAIN "Modules_MIDIFile.GUIDE


        Access this file from @{" Modules.GUIDE " LINK Modules.GUIDE/MAIN }
        to browse under AmigaGuide

@endnode


@node read_midi  "Read MIDI File"

  Read MIDI File [Read_MIDI]

                Reads a standard MIDI File and generates a MusicWeb
                "Sequence" packet that can be passed to other elements
                such as 'RePlay' for use.

                This is a 'Source' element (no inputs); each MIDI file
                read is translated into a single Sequence packet, sent
                out though its Output connector, containing all the
                information in the file.

                Its control panel has two buttons:

                    `New MIDI'     brings up a file requester from which
                                   you can select the file to be read; the
                                   resulting Sequence will be sent as soon
                                   the file is read.

                    `Resend'       re-reads and send the file that was last
                                   read without bringing up a requester.

                The default initial directory can be set in the
                command line used to launch Read_MIDI, by including
                a pathname prefixed by the `DIR' keyword.

                Both Type 0 (single track) and Type 1 (multitrack)
                files can be read, but not Type 2 (multisegment).
                All tracks of a Type 1 file are merged into a single
                sequence, so for best results each instrument should
                be on a separate MIDI channel (as is usually the case).

@endnode


@node write_midi  "Write MIDI File"

  Write MIDI File [Write_MIDI]

                Writes a standard (type 0: single track/multichannel)
                MIDI File from a MusicWeb "Sequence" packet passed to
                it from another element such as 'RePlay'.

                It is a standard `Filter' element (one feed-through
                connector).  Packets passing through aren't changed
                in any way; only Sequence packets are acknowledged
                -- all others simply continue on.

                The module has no control panel.  An arriving Sequence
                packet pops up a Save File requester so that you can
                specify where the file is to be written.

                This initial version of the module only writes type 0
                MIDIfiles.

@endnode



